{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\nLOC/size analyzer that shells `scc --format json` (deterministic, no network) and populates `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`.loc (per-file LOC + max). Absent scc -> Unavailable, never fabricated zeros.\n\n## Approach & rationale (G6/T1) — reuse the EXISTING scc parser\n`engine_b_backends` already parses scc JSON: `_scc_files(data: Any) -> list[dict[str, Any]]` returns per-file entries carrying `Code` (LOC int) and `Location` (path), consumed by `_metric_invoke` (engine_b_backends.py:376,412). REUSE that exact parser — do NOT invent a new shape. Extract `_scc_files` verbatim into `src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_scc.py` and have `engine_b_backends` import it back (single source of truth); `scc_loc.py` builds `AnalyzerResult.loc` (per-file LOC + max) from `_scc_files(json.loads(scc_stdout))`. Rationale: one parser, no drift, no new schema (T1: no novel architecture). Lives in `analyzers/` (NOT the quarantined `adapters/`). `accruing_since` = a module-level constant matching existing reader modules.\n\n## Grounding (E4/G1G2 — verified)\n- CONFIRMED engine_b_backends.py:412 `_scc_files(data) -> list[dict]` with `Code`/`Location` keys; :376 shells `[binary,\"--format\",\"json\",repo_root]`.\n- `AnalyzerResult` is created by prerequisite `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]` (depends_on edge recorded); analyzer.py is in that ticket's file_impact.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] `_scc_files` is extracted to `analyzers/_scc.py` and `engine_b_backends` imports it from there (single definition). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_single_parser` asserting `engine_b_backends._scc_files.__module__ == \"rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc\"`.\n- [ ] `scc_loc.analyze(root)` shells scc, parses via `_scc_files`, returns an `AnalyzerResult` whose `.loc.max_loc` equals the fixture max. PROVE (integration, skipif scc absent): `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_live_scc -m integration`.\n- [ ] scc absent / non-zero exit -> `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)`, not a crash and not zeros. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_absent_scc_unavailable` (monkeypatched runner raises FileNotFoundError).\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 9597, e7a0 (recorded depends_on edges).\n## Files likely touched\n- src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_scc.py (new; holds the extracted `_scc_files`)\n- src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py (new; builds AnalyzerResult.loc via `_scc_files`)\n- src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py (import `_scc_files` from the shared module)\n- tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784598639805548001,"uuid":"77c834a3-da63-4bbe-b3e5-8cde1036c731"}